cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper deals with document processing and machine learning, specifically using deep learning for table parsing. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper focuses on visual feature extraction and uses convolutional neural networks. The second likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with natural language processing in the context of document structure analysis. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper proposes a new architecture for solving a complex problem using deep learning. The fourth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper deals with training neural networks and improving performance. The fifth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) since the paper deals with analyzing the structure of documents to extract information.
